sections.Biography:
===Background===
Tommen is presented as the youngest son of [[Robert Baratheon|King Robert Baratheon]] and [[Cersei Lannister|Queen Cersei Lannister]]. Cersei and Robert made a political marriage alliance after Robert took the throne by force from the Mad King [[Aerys II Targaryen]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/houses/jbaratheon/ HBO viewer's guide, season 2 guide to houses, House Baratheon of King's Landing entry]&lt;/ref&gt; Tommen's real father is [[Jaime Lannister]], his mother's twin brother and his uncle. He has an older brother, [[File:Tyrion_and_Tommen_1x02.png|thumb|left|202px|Tyrion and Tommen]][[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey]], and an older sister [[Myrcella Baratheon|Myrcella]] with the same obfuscated parentage. Tommen is good-natured and passive in contrast to his brother Joffrey, who sometimes bullied Tommen for amusement.&lt;ref&gt;[[The Red Keep (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&lt;/ref&gt; Like his sister, he is fond of his uncle [[Tyrion Lannister]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/houses/jbaratheon/tommen-baratheon/ HBO viewer's guide, season 2 guide to houses, House Baratheon of King's Landing - Tommen Baratheon entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 1]]===
[[File:House_Baratheon_of_King's_Landing.jpg|thumb|254px|Tommen seated with the rest of the royal family at the Tourney of the Hand]]Tommen accompanies his family north to [[Winterfell]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming (episode)|Winter is Coming]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; Tommen is eating breakfast with his [[Cersei|mother]], [[Jaime Lannister|father]] and [[Myrcella Baratheon|sister]] as his uncle [[Tyrion]] approaches. He giggles as his uncle lifts him aside to join them. His sister asks whether [[Bran Stark]] will die and Tyrion replies that he is expected to live, much to Myrcellaâ&euro;&trade;s delight and Cerseiâ&euro;&trade;s horror. Tyrion goes on to say how he wishes to see [[the Wall]] and witness the â&euro;&oelig;wintry abode of the [[White Walkers|white walkers]],â&euro;? exciting Myrcella and Tommen. He then says he wants to urinate off the edge of it, a comment which causes both his niece and nephew to laugh. Cersei is irritated by his words and leaves, calling the children to her.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Tommen attends the tournament to celebrate [[Eddard Stark]] becoming [[Hand of the King]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
{{Quote|You sound like a little cat mewling for his mother.  Princes don't cry.|King [[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey I]] berating his younger brother, '''Tommen Baratheon'''.|The Old Gods and the New}}
Tommen attends [[Joffrey Baratheon|Joffrey's]] [[nameday]] [[tournament]]. He is pleased when his uncle [[Tyrion Lannister]] arrives [[File:Myrcella_Tommen_dinner_with_Sansa.jpg|thumb|left|224px|Tommen and Myrcella]]during the festivities and tells him that one day he will be as big as [[the Hound]] &quot;but much better looking&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The North Remembers]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;.

Tommen attends a dinner with [[Myrcella Baratheon|Myrcella]], [[Cersei Baratheon|his mother]] and [[Sansa Stark]]. He asks whether [[Robb Stark|Robb]] will be killed after the war, and says that he wouldn't like that.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[What is Dead May Never Die]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Myrcella is sent to [[Dorne]] as part of a marriage pact with [[House Martell]]. Tommen watches her departure from the harbor, sobbing. Joffrey mocks him for crying. As they return to the [[Red Keep]] Tyrion senses the unrest of the smallfolk and orders Tommen sent by a separate route narrowly avoiding the [[Riot of King's Landing]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Old Gods and the New]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
Tommen takes refuge in [[Maegor's Holdfast]] during the [[Battle of the Blackwater]]. Cersei takes him to the Iron Throne room when the battle seems lost. She tries to calm him with a tale about the supremacy of lions in the kingdom of beasts: the forest is full of vicious beasts, such [[File:Tommen_cries_at_Myrcella's_departure.jpg|thumb|230px|Tommen cries as Myrcella departs for [[Dorne]].]]as stags and wolves, but he is a lion, and all will bow to him. She has gotten a vial of [[Essence of Nightshade]] from Grand Maester [[Pycelle]], which is deadly if taken in more than tiny amounts and she prepares to give it to him if the city defenses fail, to grant him the mercy of a quick death instead of being captured and tormented. [[File:Cersei_and_Tommen_Blackwater_Promo.jpg|thumb|left|Cersei and Tommen during the [[Battle of Blackwater]]]]She is stopped just in time when [[Tywin Lannister]] arrives to announce their victory.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Blackwater]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
Tommen does not appear on-screen in Season 3 although he remains in King's Landing.

===[[Season 4]]===
Tommen is present at Joffrey's wedding ceremony to [[Margaery Tyrell]], and during the subsequent feast (known as the [[Purple Wedding]]). Initially, he laughed at his brother's crude play with dwarves depicting the War of the Five Kings but stopped after noticing the look upon his uncle Tyrion's face. After Joffrey's poisoning and subsequent death, Tommen inherits the crown and is now the king and ruler of the [[Seven Kingdoms]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Lion and the Rose]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;[[File:Tommen_4x02.jpg|thumb|131px|Tommen during Joffrey's Wedding Feast]]

Tommen later stands vigil with Cersei over Joffrey's corpse in the [[Great Sept of Baelor]]. [[Tywin]], in an unusually agreeable mood, enters and proceeds to grill Tommen on the traits that make a good king, ignoring Cersei's angry glares. Tommen offers holiness, justice and strength as qualities of a good king, but Tywin refutes these ideas by pointing out that Kings [[Baelor Targaryen|Baelor]], Orys, and Robert were each paragons of one of these qualities, but not very good kings. Tywin is delighted when Tommen, with minimal prompting, suggests that a good king must be wise. Tywin tells Tommen that young kings with no experience must be wise by listening to their councilors, and the wisest kings keep listening even when they don't need to anymore. As he escorts Tommen out of the Sept, Tywin begins prepping his grandson on the duties of a king's marriage. On their way out, Jaime passes them and asks how Tommen is doing; the young king replies that he is all right.&lt;ref&gt;[[Breaker of Chains]]&lt;/ref&gt;

[[File:Tommen-and-Cersei.jpg|thumb|left|226px|Tommen and Cersei mourn over Joffrey's death.]]

In response to Joffrey's death, Cersei insists that Tommen be placed under high guard, with at least four Kingsguard at his bedroom door at night, something Jaime finds a bit excessive. Tommen has been moved to Joffrey's bedchamber and has yet to redecorate; hence, he has difficulty sleeping with Joffrey's gruesome hunting trophies all around. That night [[Margaery Tyrell|Margaery]] sneaks into Tommen's chambers. She suggests that they get to know one another before their marriage, something nobles in Westeros don't usually do. Tommen is unnerved by her presence until his cat, [[Ser Pounce]], jumps up and Margaery interacts with him. Tommen sullenly reveals the cruel things Joffrey threatened to do to Ser Pounce, and he and Margaery bond over their mutual relief that they are free of him. Tommen agrees that he'd like Margaery to visit him again. Margaery departs, but not before giving a kiss on the forehead.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[File:Margaerytommen.png|thumb|224px|Margaery visits Tommen in his bedchambers.]]
[[File:Tommens-Coronation.jpg|thumb|left|260px|Tommen is crowned by the High Septon.]]
A ceremony is held in the [[Red Keep]] where the [[High Septon (After the Riot of Kingâ&euro;&trade;s Landing)|high septon]] officially crowns Tommen as king. Margaery watches from the side, and, when questioned by Cersei, notes that he sits as comfortably in the Iron Throne as if he were born to it. Cersei and Tywin later set the date of Tommen's wedding to Margaery immediately after the mourning period for Joffrey is over: a fortnight from the day of the coronation.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[First of His Name]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

On Tywin's instructions, Tommen recuses himself from presiding over Tyrion's [[Second Trial of Tyrion Lannister|trial]] for Joffrey's murder, declaring Tywin, as Hand of the King and Protector of the Realm, as his replacement. He then departs the [[Great Hall (Red Keep)|throne room]] along with two [[Kingsguard]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Laws of Gods and Men]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

